5. **Termination**: If the target node is reached during processing, its arrival time is returned. If the heap is exhausted without reaching the target, `-1` is returned indicating the node is unreachable.

This approach efficiently explores paths in the graph while leveraging the priority queue to always expand the most promising nodes first, ensuring optimal performance.

